	We'll Be Back!!!!	We stayed a whole week over the Thanksgiving Holiday and loved every minute of it. Our room was the cleanest and freshest of any hotel we have stayed in. The sheets very comfortable and a choice of pillows, either soft or firm. The view was not the greatest, but we didn't spend too much time looking out the window. Each morning we enjoyed the breakfat buffet and gathered round the craps table ($3.00 minimum, great) before it got too crowded. At first, we complained to each other that the slots were too tight, but our last night there and the morning we left, we both won. The staff is so friendly and helpful so you don't mind asking dumb questions. The room was so big, when we arrived, my husband asked me if I booked a suite. The location was convenient for us because our daughter and family live close by and we were able to forego a rental car. We took the shuttle to the strip one day and that was hassle-free. Life is good at the Suncoast Hotel and Casino.	
Nov 20 2009 	We had a great time here and would go again anytime.	We are budget travelers who love a good deal. This was a very affordable price for us ($50 for a weekend was the cheapest decent place we found in Vegas through an online search). But despite the lowest price tag, we were very impressed. The rooms are fantastic, extremely spacious, and gave us the impression we were paying much more money (I even double checked later with the cashier!). Their website said their rooms have floor to ceiling windows, though we weren't expecting much. But they were right; the entire side is all window! Sure we didn't have the greatest view, but it made for a VERY bright room. We aren't big gamblers, so we can't comment on the games, but everything seemed to be available. They have an enormous sports betting lounge, and even a bowling alley. Everyone we dealt with was very friendly, from the clerk who gave us a couple free drink and food coupons to the cocktail waitresses. One thing to note: we may have just had a good night, but the drink service was BY FAR the quickest we have had in recent times. Very impressive!This casino is NOT on the strip, but they do offer shuttle services to and from, so if you want to spend just an evening there like we did, it's perfect.Cons are the confusing location of the elevator and the fact that registration is right in the heart of the casino. But that is only an issue when you first arrive and bring your bags in. After you know where everything is, that location is convenient.All in all, it's great value that will leave you thinking you'd just spent more.	
