Dec 21 2008 	Good price but not great for business purposes	I recently stayed at the Suncoast while on business in Las Vegas. The hotel is located in Summerlin, about 20 minutes from the Strip. My room was large and well maintained. It had a great view of the valley. I had read quite a few complaints about the beds at this hotel but I found that, while it was very firm, my bed was comfortable. As reported, there is no choice of pillows. There was a large plasma TV in the room as well as a refrigerator. TV channel selection was very limited. The bathroom was large with great water pressure. Housekeeping kept my room is good shape.The casino is the focal point of the hotel. You have to drag your luggage through it to get to the elevator, which I find very inconvenient. It was also very smokey, so much so that I could only stand it for short periods of time. There are several restaurants in the facility. I had dinner in both Salvatore's and SC Prime and both were good but not great. Since I was traveling for business, I left the hotel fairly early. I found that breakfast was a problem. The buffet did not open until 8 a.m. and the bagel cafe didn't open until 8:30 a.m. This left a small coffee shop in the lobby that served a small selection of pastry. A muffin and OJ was about $7. If you need the internet, plan on spending an additional $13 per day.If you're looking for an &quot;off strip&quot; hotel for a reasonable price and you want to gamble, this may be a good option. If you need business services (like breakfast in the morning) and want to be close to Las Vegas attractions, I'd look elsewhere.	
