tter of apology with the coupon, just the coupon itself in an envelope that I had to retrieve from the front desk. Guess it was again too much trouble to slip under my door.If you didn't have a battery operated alarm clock and needed to get up in the morning, you were in trouble. Did I mention that housekeeping never bothered to set the clock again after the power was off? The blinking clock flashed the wrong time for the remainder of the stay.Best advice, run don't walk from this hotel.	
