Aug 19 2008 	Best hotel in Vegas	This is a great hotel for someone who doesn't want to deal with the hussle of the strip. The rooms are huge and the view is amazing. Not much of a selection when it comes to room service, but the hotel is located in Summerlin and is surrounded by restaurants, grocery stores, and only a few minutes drive from the red rock mountains. The area, unlike the strip, is very safe and is a great place for families to stay. The only drawback is walking through the casino and trying to find the elevators, but this is the case in all Vegas hotels. Every time I stay here the room rate has been under $50, which is a steal.	
