Jun 6 2008	Great Hotel but far from strip	I've stayed at the Suncoast twice and have enjoyed both of my stays.HOTEL:The hotel itself is very nice. It has casino, movie theater, and a small pool. The rooms are huge with a large bathroom and very large area. It can easily fit a family of four. The casino was a good size, and the minimums weren't as ridiculous as some of the strip hotels. Also, their bingo hall is apparently the happening place. LOCATION:This hotel is approximately 20 to 30 minutes drive from the strip. If you plan on hanging out at the strip, this is not the place to stay. However, they do have a lot of markets, Darling Tennis Center, and golf courses nearby.FOOD:They had quite a few restaurants at the hotel. The range of food was mediocre to awful. Don't eat at the cafe place with Chinese food because I heard it was terrible. The buffet was nothing to rave about either. I never tried the Italian or steak place, but it doesn't look too spectacular either.If you want a big room and don't mind a location far from the strip, this is a nice place to stay.	
