May 10 2008 	Exceptionally quiet rooms	We and several couples stayed at the Suncoast Hotel for four nights in mid-April when our son was getting married at the Stratosphere. We picked this hotel after reading the reviews on Trip Advisor. We were surprised you had to walk through the casino to get to your room, but that seems pretty standard in Vegas. Our rooms were large and exceptionally quiet, (though not on the golf course view side), the pool was beautiful (and not crowded), and we loved being away from the Strip. Our requests to stay on the same floor with family and friends were honored, and when my sister-in-law's room's hair dryer caught on fire, it was replaced within the hour. One of our family members stayed at Treasure Island through a Costco package deal (airfare, car, hotel), and it was definitely cheaper, but it is on the Strip. We had no complaints about the staff or service at this hotel, and would stay there again.	
