 by the same 24 hour restaurant, and asked to have order to go, in a box, because of how slow the service was last time. she told us no, they didn't have any take out silverware. so instead, we ordered room service, which was the same exact menu, but 4x the prices, and they bring you regular silverware. not really sure why they wouldn't just give us a roll of silverware, like they did when they delivered our $30 appetizer meal, ridiculous!we didn't use the pool or the gym, so can't comment on those, but the movies and the bowling alley looked very nice. the gift shop, was quite nice, had everything we needed and both ladies working in there were so nice and helpful. when it came time to check out, it was very easy, did it right on the tv. called down to the bellman and asked for a luggage cart, as we had 4 big bags. he told us it would be over an hour wait, so we had to make 2 trips down ourselves. all in all, the facility was very clean, including had sanitizer units on the walls. the customer service was pretty poor, which to me is a big reason people become repeat customers. not sure if we will stay here again, when we come out to visit our family, who live only 2 miles away. it seemed like the staff could have cared less about all the people who spent our hard earned cash to stay there, and i didn't care for that attitude at all	
Apr 26 2008 	Short Stay in Vegas	On our way to visit Las Vegas relatives and national parks in Utah, we stayed at the Suncoast Casino and Hotel and found that it fit our needs perfectly. The facility is located some distance from both the airport and the &quot;Strip&quot;, but is easy to get to by car. For a very, very modest price, our room was huge, clean, and had great views from the 8th floor. As in most Las vegas hotels, one enters by walking through the casino, which has, I believe, an area of 80,000 square feet or about an hectare. Various restaurants are scattered around the perimeter of the casino. The neighboring vicinity contains several golf courses and a large shopping mall. All is clean and shining brightly in the desert sun.	
