Mar 3 2008	Highly Recommended	I can only second what others have said here. Clean, crisp, sunny and well-maintained hotel. So as not to waste space, let me add something I rarely read in reviews: an overview of the area surrounding the hotel.Suncoast is not on or near the Strip. It's a good 7-10 miles from it but that's part of the appeal. The hotel is at the edge of a golf course and surrounded by upscale condos and single-family homes. It's very quiet--more like a resort community than a gambling one.Some rooms have views of the Strip in the distance (looks incredible at night), others have view of the golf course and the mountains and Red Rock Canyon (very nice to wake up to).Good breakfast deal: for the price of eggs and bacon in the casual dining restaurant off the casino floor (I forget its name), you can have the breakfast buffet. Many hot, fresh choices that border on brunch but also a very good yoghurt and cereal bar.I can't imagine staying on the Strip. Rent a car and have the freedom to play all you want and then go home for a good night's sleep in one of the best neighborhoods in Vegas.	
