Dec 28 2007 	An unexpected gem	We booked one of the suites for six nights in Dec of '07 and were pleasantly surprised by the size and amenities in the room - not what one would expect from a Summerlin hotel... more like a high-roller suite at a strip hotel with a nice view of the Strip off in the distance in one direction and Red Rocks in the other.Room and amenities were excellent with a very nicely appointed bathroom. Unfortunately, the shower head pressure was about a 5 out of 10.Restaurants were all of good quality - don't expect 3 star and you won't be disappointed. Like most of the off-strip properties, the entire staff was friendly and accommodating from the housekeepers to the dealers to the pit bosses and desk staff.As with most Vegas properties, the smoke in the casino is unbearable but, fortunately, it didn't make it up to the 10th floor.	
Dec 24 2007 	The Suncoast is a Great Place to Stay!	We stayed for an extended weekend. We paid $47 for Friday and Saturday night, and $25 for Sunday (yes, really.) The room was fantastic. It was very spacious, much larger than an average hotel room. The room had a large flat screen tv, was very clean, and the beds were quite comfortable. The view was beautiful. We looked down at the pool, golf course, and dessert mountains in the distance. (Request the pool side, because the other side views were not as nice.) The pool and pool area looked very nice, but we were unable to use, because it was too cold. Our room was non-smoking and it didn't even smell like smoke in the hallway. This was a big plus, considering the haze of smoke in the casino. The bowling alley and theater were also spacious and nice.If you want to stay off the strip, you can't beat this place. The drive to the strip was easy on the freeways and took only 10 minutes.As mentioned in other reviews, the restaurant prices were fair and the buffet was good. The best surprise was the prices in the hotel store. A six pack of beer was about $6. About the same you'd find in a grocery store. The other alcohol was similarly priced.Regarding the price we paid per night, after a rather exhaustive search, I booked on i4vegas.com. It had by far the best rates. The hotel was asking $144 for the nights we paid $47, on their website. So, shop around and give the Suncoast I try. I'm so glad we did!	
