Sep 6 2007 	Not bad for an all-in-one.	The Suncoast is an all-in-one stay: Hotel, casino, restaurants, bowling alley, convenience store, and movie theater. The rooms themselves were nice, with reasonably comfortable beds, lots of space, nice bathrooms, and good cleanliness. I wasn't impressed with the restaurants except for the steakhouse, which was priced reasonably and produced an excellent meal. The casino itself is not extensive, and I didn't spend any time in there. If you have kids, be aware that the floor-waitress outfits are rather racy!My biggest complaint was the HIGH cost of in-room internet access. It was the most expensive I've come across yet ($17 a day!)Overall, everything about this hotel was average or above average. I wasn't overly impressed... but it definitely had about the lowest cost in the area, so it was worth it for the money.	
