Mar 31 2007 	We love staying at the Suncoast	We go to Las Vegas once a year and have stayed at different hotels, but the last 4 years we have stayed at the Suncoast and we love it. The rooms are huge and the view is wonderful. It even has a big bathroom and you don't find that too often. We always ask for the mountain view and it overlooks the pool, golf course and the beautiful mountains. It is breath taking. The hotel is not that far from Red Rock Canyon. The hotel staff is very friendly. We have never had a problem there. They have great restaurants. Several to choose from. We love eating at the buffet or the Mexican restaurant. They are pretty reasonable. They have a 64 lane bowling alley and other areas for kids to enjoy. Most anything you need you will find there. If not there are nearby stores. They have a shuttle that will take you to and from the strip free of charge if you are a guest at the hotel so you won't have to bother driving there. They have plenty of good slots, tables and even bingo. They also have movie theaters. We feel very comfortable and safe when we stay there. They have plenty of security. You can't go up the elevators in the evening unless you show security your room key. When you check in they give you fun books and they have discounts in them. Like I said we love it and we are looking forward to our trip this year. We would highly reccommend this hotel if you like being away from the really busy districts like the strip.Larry &amp; Sandra (from Mobile, AL)	
