Sep 25 2006 	Beautiful Rooms	It was a little bit farther away than what some of the reviews made out, some said 20 min. I don't think so, unless you drive 100 miles per hour and know exactly where you are going. The shuttle took around 30-40 minutes. Other than that it was very nice. Make sure when you pull in that you go to the lobby, valet service, do not park yourself, we did and ended up dragging our luggage everywhere, until we decided to get back into the van, and park at the east side and still had to drag a little bit.The casino is pretty big, and pretty popular for being so far away from the others. I didn't think the smoke was so bad, I am a non-smoker and it did not bother me that much. The buffet was pretty big, several different stations of food (mexican, seafood, mongolian, chinese, american and italian and a huge desert station) tried some things i have never had before. The flavor of the food average, some even a little bland. We ate there only once. The second place we ate at was the Cafe Sienna and the food is great and they have large portions with fair prices. This is the restaraunt that also does room service. Having kids with us this is the only restaraunt that we ate at.And finally the rooms are huge and beautiful, make sure you get the view with the mountains and golf courses, you also can look down at the pool (which was never busy). Bathrooms were huge, seperate room for the toilet and tub. Double sink in the counter room. And a huge 37 inch tv in your living area, you can order movies for 11.00, we didn't though. You have your bowling, arcade and movie theatre if bored with the casino. Bowling prices were fair, and on Wednesdays they had 1.00 draft beer specials.This is a very clean casino, everywhere you look the employees were cleaning up.Payouts on the machines were ok, my mother did alright, won over 1000.00, and one night i heard alot of yelling and screaming over by the tables, someone was having a lucky night.**Negatives: The casino was freezing, I felt sorry for the cocktail waitresses they have very skimpy outifts. If you want cab service you have to make arrangements 24 hours in advance,(we found out the hard way and was late for the mystere show by 20 minutes). It is a bit far away, but after being 1 day on the strip who cares. Hope you have a wonderful time!	
Sep 5 2006 	Nice Hotel	We stayed at the Suncoast during Labor Day weekend. The place is about 20 minutes from the Strip, but it was fine because we had a rental car. The place was sold out all weekend, so although I had requested a non-smoking room, by the time I checked in on Saturday, they only had smoking rooms left. Let me say, if you are not a smoker, being in a smoking room is really difficult! I know I'm in Vegas and all, but it doesn't mean I need to be around smoke in my own room! Well, they were able to switch us to a non-smoking room the next day which was great. The hotel is nice, nothing spectacular, but it's clean and it has all the amentities you would want (pool, restaurants, casino, covered free parking). We had breakfast at Cafe Sienna. The food was good and our waitress, Pearl, was a doll! She's a local, so she gave us all these tips around driving around the Strip. We also had breakfast one morning at the Bagel Express which was good as well. Prices at all these places are reasonable.The room was very spacious and it had 37&quot; flat screen tv. My husband loved that.	
Sep 5 2006 	Very nice stay	We stayed at the Suncoast on our way back from a California trip. We got a very nice rate for the Sunday before Labor Day, especially considering holiday hotel rates in Las Vegas. We'd stayed at the Orleans before, which is owned by the same hotel group, and chose this hotel based on the great stay that we'd experienced at the Orleans.Check-in went quite smoothly, without a long wait at the reception desk. We went to our assigned room, but instead of having the 2 beds we'd requested, there was only a king bed and sofa, which didn't work for our party of 3. We called the front desk, and they switched us to a different room with 2 beds.The rooms are very large, with a nice flat panel TV that my husband and grown son loved. The beds are comfortable, but their linens and pillows could use updating. We liked the way the bathrooms are arranged, with 2 sinks outside the toilet/shower area, which made it convenience with 3 of us trying to shower and get ready in the morning. Our room was non-smoking, and the entire floor is also non-smoking, which helps to eliminate any smoke smell.We did go bowling. The bowling area is large, with 64 lanes, and it's nice to have something to do that isn't gambling associated.As other travelers have mentioned, it's extremely smokey in the casino area. We didn't spend any time there, but it was annoying even walking through. My main complaint about the hotel is the way it's laid out. You have to parade through the casino with your luggage. It would be nice if there was a separate entrance for hotel guests that bypassed the casino.We will definitely be staying at the Coast hotels again.	
Aug 22 2006	Decent Room GREAT View....	We stayed at the Suncoast for four nights in mid--August. The hotel is about 20 minutes from the Strip, depending on traffic. The rooms were generally fine (although the lack of a minibar/fridge seemed odd to me), but the view of the Red Rock Park was absolutely astonishing! The floor-to-ceiling windows in our room on the fourth floor gave us an absolutely stunning view of the hills. The view alone was worth the room cost--make sure to ask for a room with a view!Other oddities included the lack of a concierge and the way in which the registration desk was hidden among the slot machines. Given the price, we would certainly stay here again, but it is certainly a mid-priced casino, not the Bellagio!	
