Apr 22 2006 	Great Hotel - Very Off Strip	My wife and I recently stayed at the Suncoast from April 9 - 13. I was there for work and this hotel was near the location I was working. Compared to the hotels on this strip this is a nice quiet place. It is definately a &quot;locals&quot; casino with most of the clientel from neighboring areas. When we first pulled up the giant gold windows on the outside looked great. Inside the casino was open enough to get around without bumping into everyone and every machine which was a nice change from a lot of others we have visited. Check-in on a Sunday afternoon at 3:00 was very easy, no line at all. The only complaint was that we ended up with 2 queens instead of a king that we prefer, the lady at the counter said they were all booked up that night. Since I didn't reserve the room (my work did) it wasn't specified that I wanted a king, so no big deal, and not the hotels fault. The main part of the room was an above average hotel room with 2 queens a work desk, cabinet with a 25ish&quot; TV, and a lounge chair and ottoman. Some very above average features were the windows - 3 giant floor to celing windows that took up the whole wall, and the bathroom which had a huge counter with two sinks and a seperate room for the toilet and shower. The walls were a very nice tile which was spotless. The shower had the tile and was also spotless and had great water pressure and drained just fine, something I've found many hotels do not. One thing we were looking forward to was the view, but it was just ok. There are some high rise condo's being built and that is what our room faced, but off to one side were the mountains, and off to the other side was the strip way off in the distance. We could see all those, but the condos were our main view. We ate at 4 different restaurants there:1. The St. Tropez buffet - This was a really good deal we ate here three times, the night we arrived, once for a regular breakfast and then came back later on after we had checked out and ate here for their Easter buffet. Both times the food was fresh and the selection had something for everyone from Chinese/Mongolian to Mexican to Italian to meat and potatoes. Also, the desert bar was huge. Each time we were there the service was wonderful. Plates always picked up right away and drinks kept full. 2. Cafe Siena - This was quite good as well. We had dinner there one evening and I ordered off of their chinese menu which was good. Again, the service was exceptional. Very friendly and attentive. They had a great breakfast special too, for $1.95 they had 2 plate size pancakes, 2 eggs and sausage. I was filled up for the rest of the day after that. I was alone that morning so I had brought a book to read and the waitress made sure my coffee and water were kept full as long as I was there, never rushed to get me out of there, which I thought was really nice.3. Senor Miguels - This was a good restaurant, but not as great as the others listed above. I had the red snapper and it was very tasty. Nothing too memorable about this place though.4. Via Veneto - This was quite good, we got there right at 5 and the place was almost empty. The atmosphere was very elegant, but people were dressed in everything from shorts to suits. The food was good italian, and the service was great when it was empty, but when we were getting ready to leave the place was filled up and it took 30 minutes for me to get my credit card back after I went to pay, so I was not impressed with that.Some other notes about this hotel/casino/resort. They have a 16 screen movie theater, a bowling ally that we never got around to using, but both looked quite nice. Also, they have bingo which my wife loved going to the 9AM bingo session because they gave out free donuts. I liked that she went too because she ended up winning $275 one morning. I never had a chance to use the pool, although it was open until 11:00 in the evening. However, my wife did and said it was fine.We did use the shuttle to the strip a couple times, and time is completely dependant on traffic. Once it took about 15min with completely open roads. The other time when we had our luggage because we were moving the the Barbary Coast it took 45min but traffic was stop and go (mostly stop). Overall we were very happy with how clean and how good this service was. The location is a long way from the strip, so not a place for 1st timers, but it is a much more laid back atmosphere than the strip hotels are. We would definately consider staying here again even for a vacation, and possibly never leave the hotel.	
Mar 17 2006	Clean quietreasonable	We stayed here specifically to AVOID the strip and are glad we did. The room was large and very clean,the shower had excellent water pressure, we heard no noise from people walking down the hall openig doors etc., and we heard nothing from the casino. Yes, the casino was smokey but what casino isn't? The servers do dress in skimpy outfits, but not any more so than any other casino, and the dealers, wait staff, front desk personnel, and house-keeping were really nice, friendly and helpful. Be sure to ask for a room with a mountain view, it is spectacular. The breakfast buffet is worth the money, the Mexican restaurant is so-so, and the Cafe Sienna is a B to B-(don't get the french fries.) We didn't try Primos, but highly recommend The Steakhouse at Circus Circus. Yes we know the Hotel Circus Circus is a dump but the restaurant is GREAT. Since the weather was cool we didn't use the pool but it was sparkling clean and the workout room was a reasonable size. Overall I would stay here again and liked it as much as The Venetian with half the price tag. (Travel Now WebSite 84.99 per night!) The one thing I didn't like was their shampoo but my husband didn't mind it.	
