Feb 27 2006 	Not if you want to see Vegas	This is a fine hotel and casino if you don't need a shuttle from the airport or don't want to see the strip. The shuttle from the airport runs at on 2 to 4 hour interval. If you in after 11am the next shuttle is not until 3pm. A taxi is about $50. The hotel is about 25 minutes from the strip in traffic and the shuttles to the strip are not very convenient either. The casino is veryu smoky and you have to go through it to get to the rooms. The rooms are very large and nice and I would consider them above average to excellent. If not for the terrible shuttle service I would have rated this hotel much higher. If you don't want to leave or have a vehicle this would be a nice place to stay.	
