Sep 22 2005 	Clean rooms but couldn't escape cigarette smoke	I stayed at the Suncoast while attending a business seminar recently. My room was clean and comfortable, but I couldn't escape the overwhelming cigarette and cigar smoke from the casino. All of the hotel's amenities (restaurants, movie theaters, conference rooms, bowling alleys) were accessible through the casino, so I couldn't avoid the haze. My health definitely suffered from the stay. I nearly checked-out when I discovered that the large picture window in my room couldn't be opened for ventilation. The Suncoast has nice amenities but toxic air ruined my experience. I was not offered bell service when I checked-in even though I caught a fleeting glimpse of someone in a uniform that looked to a bell person. The front desk was small, understaffed, and had no lobby, and my line snaked-out into a row of slot machines. Finding the hotel elevators from the front desk was is a challenge and best left to the adventuresome. The Suncoast hotel is an afterthought to the casino. This was not the &quot;resort&quot; that I expected and I would not stay there again. I would also recommend against bringing adolescent boys to the Suncoast, unless exposing them to waitresses in lingerie too hot for Victoria's Secret isn't a problem for your family.	
